  "prompt": "Can gravity slow time?",
  "response": "Yes, gravity can slow down time, a phenomenon known as gravitational time dilation. According to Einstein's theory of general relativity, the stronger the gravitational field, the slower time passes. This means:\n\n1. Time moves slightly slower near massive objects like planets or stars\n2. Time passes more quickly in areas of weaker gravity, like high altitudes\n3. Clocks at sea level tick slightly slower than clocks at the top of a mountain\n4. GPS satellites must account for this time difference to maintain accuracy\n\nThe more massive an object and the closer you are to it, the more significant the time dilation effect becomes. Near extremely massive objects like black holes, time can slow down dramatically.",
